snippet: The world’s bank of digital information is growing at a rate of five trillion bits a second, and there’s a lot going on inside that we don’t know about.
abstract: Dennis Overbye essay considers the implications of the swirling universe of data created by the Internet, which grows at a rate of five trillion bits per second; notes that some theorists think the digital world has its own scientific laws, and that its evolution will likely proceed with unforeseen consequences.
lead_paragraph: The world’s bank of digital information is growing at a rate of five trillion bits a second, and there’s a lot going on inside that we don’t know about.

headline.print_headline: Mystery of Big Data’s Parallel Universe Brings Fear, and a Thrill
